{
  "text": "for any homogeneous a ∈ V and m, n ∈ Z. An admissible V -module M is said to be irreducible if M has no non-trivial admissible weak V -submodule. When an admissible V -module M is a direct sum of irreducible admissible submodules, M is called completely reducible. A vertex operator algebra V is said to be rational if any admissible V -module is completely reducible. It was proved in [CITATION_1] that if V is rational then there are only finitely many irreducible admissible V -modules up to isomorphism.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "16478871"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "16478871": {
      "title": "Twisted representations of vertex operator algebras",
      "abstract": "This paper gives an analogue of Ag(V) theory for a vertex operator superalgebra V and an automorphism g of finite order. The relation between the g-twisted V-modules and Ag(V)-modules is established. It is proved that if V is g-rational, then Ag(V) is finite-dimensional semi-simple associative algebra and there are only finitely many irreducible g-twisted V-modules."
    }
  }
